author: Tim McGovern
title: ‘Cash Me Outside’ Girl Flashes Grill And Fans Dollar Bills In Music Video
text:
Like Us On Facebook Like Us On Facebook 
After becoming a viral sensation following her appearance (and reappearance on Thursday) on Dr. Phil where she admitted to stealing cars and delivered the iconic “Cash me outside, how bow dah?” line, Danielle Bregoli is using her new fame to come out swinging. 
Sorry, that was kind of insensitive seeing as how she literally punched someone on an airplane . 
While TSA agents might not be a fan of the 13-year-old, that won’t stop all of us from enjoying this new music video from Kodak Black that stars Danielle. 
Have you watched the whole thing? Perfect. So have I (27 times) Let’s discuss… because I have a lot of questions. 
First of all, what’s going on with this grill? Giphy 
I haven’t seen a grill moment this awkward since Michael Scott burned his foot on a George Forman grill. 
Also, Danielle is looking at the camera the same way we all look at our crushes when they walk in the room. 
It’s that face when you want to flirt, but your facial muscles decide to be cringeworthy instead. 
Next, let’s discuss this “make it rain” moment. Giphy 
Who makes it rain by flicking their money as if it were a bug? 
Her face looks so scared, too. It’s basically how I look when I get my paycheck and blow half of it at the racetrack (come on, Stinky Pete! You’ve gotta win sometime!). 
Although, I’ve got to hand it to this music video. Allow me to explain with a short checklist. 
Cash? Check. 
Outside? Check. 
How bow dah? 
That’s three for three… exactly the same as the judges who ruled in favor of not reinstating Trump’s travel ban. 
Coincidence? There are no coincidences. 
Honestly, I wish Danielle all the best. Perhaps, she can learn from her fame and maybe (just maybe) get some anger management.
